f=Executive Office/echo/custom/investor-update-template/SKILL.md · in=investor-update-template recurring monthly/quarterly production process sending investor updates distinct `investor-update-generator` (marketplace), which supplies actual template scoring rubric skill uses rather reinvents. skill workflow around template: collect, draft, enforce honesty, validate, review, approve, send. · p=Make sending credible, honest investor update repeatable, low-friction monthly process rather one-off scramble time while enforcing hard "no spin" rule underlying marketplace skill partially covers. · wu=Triggers: "monthly update," "investor email," "quarterly update," "send investor update," it's time cadence (monthly early-stage, quarterly later-stage, `investor-update-generator`'s cadence guidance) produce one. · st:/ Protocol=`Collect metrics + context \· -> Draft using investor-update-generator's template \· -> Enforce: at least one honest lowlight, minimum (hard rule, not optional) \· -> Validate with investor-update-generator's scoring script \· -> Triple-pass review` · h3:Phase 1 — Collect=Pull period's metrics wherever operator says they're tracked don't assume source. pull: last update sent (for continuity/delta), current open asks, any known wins misses since last update. · h3:Phase 2 — Draft=Draft using `investor-update-generator`'s `assets/investor_update_template.md` structure (highlights, lowlights, metrics table, product, sales/GTM, team, asks, looking ahead) don't build separate template scratch. · h3:Phase Enforce Honesty Rule=hard rule specific skill, stricter underlying marketplace skill's scoring (which penalizes updates *entirely* positive): **every update include least one genuine lowlight, risk, miss** manufactured, omitted either one exists. period genuinely lowlights worth naming, say explicitly update rather silently having none suspiciously perfect update flagged unusual, treated normal). · h3:Phase 4 — Validate=Run draft through `investor-update-generator`'s `scripts/investor_update_validator.py`. Treat score below ready send address specific missing/weak sections flags before proceeding. · h3:Phase Triple-Pass Review=Three distinct passes, one combined skim: **Accuracy pass** number claim checks out against source metrics Phase **Tone/spin pass** check specifically failure mode marketplace skill's rubric miss: technically-present-but-buried lowlights, lowlights stated softly they read wins. **Specificity pass** ask passes test "could investor act without further clarification?" (from `investor-update-generator`'s reference guide) vague asks get rewritten cut. · h3:Phase 6 — Approval=Route sign-off whatever agent's escalation config specifies (see leader agent's `operational/agent/` config pattern) hardcode specific person role. approval routing configured yet, default asking operator directly before send. · h3:Phase 7 — Send=Send whatever channel/tool actually configured assume specific delivery mechanism. none configured, produce final update file/draft hand operator send manually. · of=`### Pre-Send Checklist \· - [ ] At least one honest lowlight included \· - [ ] Validator score: [score]/100 \· - [ ] Accuracy pass complete \· - [ ] Tone/spin pass complete` · of=structure `investor-update-generator`'s template, plus short pre-send checklist appended: · pr=spin, ever lowlight exists gets omitted worse failure rough update includes it., Don't duplicate marketplace skill's template validator extend enforce top them., Consistency across periods metric definitions shouldn't change month month (same principle marketplace skill's reference guide states); flag explicitly definition needs change, rather quietly redefining. · f=`investor-update-generator`'s validator script isn't available reason, scoring checks manually reasoning through rule list don't skip validation entirely., metrics can't sourced period, flag exactly which missing rather drafting around gap vague language., lowlight honestly identified, state explicitly flag worth double-checking rather presenting all-positive update normal. · b:with Other echo Skills=Depends `investor-update-generator` (marketplace) template validator don't rebuild here., Distinct `pitch-narrative`: pitch-narrative occasional/one-off fundraising story; skill recurring operational update. Facts stay consistent between two, they serve different moments.